OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,465,460,260,120,000,100
PN,46406
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F464A1781111161
OL,3,COvercrowded prisons in Wales
OL,4,Cundermining safety, MPs warn
OL,6,FMPs are also calling for the MoJ to
OL,7,Fconfirm its plan for the Swansea
OL,8,FResidential Women's Centre, including
OL,9,Fwhether it will open and when.
OL,11,FThere are no women's prisons in Wales,
OL,12,Fwith Welsh women who receive custodial
OL,13,Fsentences being held in England, which
OL,14,Fthe report says poses challenges for
OL,15,Fresettlement and rehabilitation.
OL,17,FThe rehabilitation centre was due to
OL,18,Fopen two years ago but, after funding
OL,19,Fwas reallocated by the previous UK
OL,20,FGovernment, it remains unclear whether
OL,21,Fthe project will go ahead.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G6/7
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,465,460,260,120,000,100
PN,46407
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F464A1781111161
OL,3,COvercrowded prisons in Wales
OL,4,Cundermining safety, MPs warn
OL,6,FThe committee said "the centre should
OL,7,Fsupport women who have committed low-
OL,8,Flevel offences to address the root
OL,9,Fcauses of their offending behaviour,
OL,10,Ftherefore being a genuine alternative
OL,11,Fto custody: not a prison in all but
OL,12,Fname."
OL,14,FAn MoJ spokesperson said the current
OL,15,FUK Government had "inherited a prison
OL,16,Fsystem in crisis" but that they "are
OL,17,Fdelivering the largest expansion of
OL,18,Fprison places since the Victorian era
OL,19,Fand aim to deliver hundreds of new
OL,20,Fplaces in Wales."
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G7/7
